CA. 1942
PAN AMERICAN AIRWAYS, INC.
EXPERIENCE AND QUALIFICATIONS OF HAROLD M. BIXBY
Harold M. Bixby is Vice President of Pan American
Airways, Inc., supervising the operations of the Atlantic,
Pacific and Alaska divisions, and of those of China National
Aviation Corporation, a Pan American affiliate.
Mr. Bixby became associated with Pan American Air-
ways in 1932, and from then until May, 1938, he served as
Far Eastern Representative of Pan American Airways, supervis-
ing the operations of China National Aviation Corporation. He
was also responsible for the negotiation of operating rights
and other projects having to do with the inauguration of the
transpacific service.
On May 31, 1938, after his return to
New York, he was elected Vice President
of
Pan American Air-
ways, Inc., which position he now holds.
On May 21, 1942,
he was elected a member of the Board of Directors of Pan
American Airways, Inc., and
at various times in the past he
has served as a director of Detroit Aircraft Corporation,
Transcontinental Air Transport Company, Central States Life
Insurance Company, Emerson Electric Manufacturing Company,
Lambert Pharmacal Company, Mississippi Valley Trust Company,
and Missouri Portland Cement Companyâ€¢
From 1920 to 1929 he was Vice President of the State
National Bank of St. Louis, and in 1927-28 he served as Presi-
dent of the St. Louis Chamber of Commerce.
